type.description:

A <a href='type://SourceSet'>SourceSet</a> represents a logical group of Java source and resources. 
<p> 
See the example below how <a href='type://SourceSet'>SourceSet</a> 'main' is accessed and how the <a href='type://SourceDirectorySet'>SourceDirectorySet</a> 'java' 
is configured to exclude some package from compilation. 

<pre autoTested=''> 
apply plugin: 'java' 

sourceSets { 
      exclude 'some/unwanted/package/**' 
    } 
  } 
} 
</pre>

method.description:

Returns the name of the compile classpath configuration for this source set. 
<br><br><b class='return'>returns:</b>The compile classpath configuration 

@since 2.12


Returns the name of the compile only configuration for this source set. 
<br><br><b class='return'>returns:</b>The compile only configuration name 

@since 2.12

